{"body": "<p>It's a known problem in <code>Spark 2.0.1</code> (<a href=\"https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-17816\" rel=\"nofollow\">SPARK-17816</a>) and will be fixed with <code>Spark 2.0.2/2.1.0</code> (<a href=\"https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/15425\" rel=\"nofollow\">related pull request</a>).</p>\n\n<p>To get rid of the exception without waiting for <code>Spark 2.0.2/2.1.0</code>, clone the <a href=\"https://github.com/apache/spark/tree/branch-2.0\" rel=\"nofollow\">latest, unstable spark version</a> and <a href=\"http://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/programming-guide.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">build apache-spark manually</a>. </p>\n", "tags": ["apache-spark"], "creation_date": 1477679797, "score": 1, "last_activity_date": 1477679797, "answer_id": 40311270, "is_accepted": true, "owner": {"user_id": 1646364, "reputation": 665, "user_type": "registered", "accept_rate": 82, "display_name": "Sascha Vetter", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/1646364/sascha-vetter", "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4705f2f76d3a78bc3a2a21c29722db8e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1"}, "title": "Spark Listener EventLoggingListener threw an exception / ConcurrentModificationException", "question_id": 40286001}